HEADWORD: Glen
<hw>Glen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Celtic origin; cf. W.
<ets>glyn</ets> a deep valley, Ir. & Gael. <ets>gleann</ets> valley,
glen.]</ety> <def>A secluded and narrow valley; a dale; a depression
between hills.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And wooes the widow's daughter of the <qex>glen</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Glengarry bonnet</ent>⟦br⟧
